{
  "texts": [
    "Considering the overall limited evidence for the quality of the scales, I will formulate recommendations drawing mainly from the COSMIN priorities considering content validity the most important measurement property, the scales' potential for efficient revalidation, and the target populations.",
    "When aiming for an assessment of general population, AILS 36 is the scale with the most robust quality evidence.",
    "It showed at least some evidence for content validity and reliability, while showing good evidence for structural validity and internal consistency.",
    "Also, it has been revalidated in another two studies 46, 47.",
    "Pinski & Belian's instrument 44 also showed at least some evidence for content validity, but it has been validated on a limited sample, requiring revalidation on a bigger sample in the future."
  ]
}